{"id":38783,"date":"2023-02-13T10:42:05","date_gmt":"2023-02-13T06:42:05","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/?p=38783"},"modified":"2024-09-17T12:07:24","modified_gmt":"2024-09-17T08:07:24","slug":"righteous-intercede","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2023\/02\/13\/righteous-intercede\/","title":{"rendered":"Hadith on Intercession: Righteous intercede for sinful brethren"},"content":{"rendered":"<p>Abu Sa\u2019id al-Khudri reported: The Prophet, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \u201c<strong>By the One in whose hand is my soul, none among you are more fervent to claim a right from Allah on the Day of Resurrection than the believers on behalf of their brothers in the Hellfire. They will say: Our Lord, they fasted, prayed, and performed pilgrimage with us! It will be said to them: Take out those whom you recognize. Thus, the Hellfire is forbidden for their bodies and they will take out many people.<\/strong>\u201d<\/p>\n<p>Source: S\u0323ah\u0323i\u0304h\u0323 al-Bukha\u0304ri\u0304 7439, S\u0323ah\u0323i\u0304h\u0323 Muslim 183<\/p>\n<p>Grade:\u00a0<strong><em>Muttafaqun Alayhi<\/em><\/strong>\u00a0(authenticity agreed upon) according to Al-Bukhari and Muslim<\/p>\n<p style=\"text-align: right;\">\u0639\u064e\u0646\u0652 \u200c\u0623\u064e\u0628\u0650\u064a \u0633\u064e\u0639\u0650\u064a\u062f\u064d \u0627\u0644\u0652\u062e\u064f\u062f\u0652\u0631\u0650\u064a\u0650\u0651 \u0623\u064e\u0646\u064e\u0651 \u0627\u0644\u0646\u064e\u0651\u0628\u0650\u064a\u064e\u0651 \u0635\u064e\u0644\u064e\u0651\u0649 \u0627\u0644\u0644\u0647\u064f \u0639\u064e\u0644\u064e\u064a\u0652\u0647\u0650 \u0648\u064e\u0633\u064e\u0644\u064e\u0651\u0645\u064e \u0642\u064e\u0627\u0644\u064e \u0648\u064e\u0627\u0644\u0651\u064e\u0630\u0650\u064a \u0646\u064e\u0641\u0652\u0633\u0650\u064a \u0628\u0650\u064a\u064e\u062f\u0650\u0647\u0650 \u0645\u064e\u0627 \u0645\u0650\u0646\u0652\u0643\u064f\u0645\